values: bored & tired of watching the same full house episodes over and over again so ive decided to update. ive come to the conclusion that lisles a pretty boring town, not much goin on all the time..but we manage to make it fun. last night we had absolutely nothing to do so me kels maggz kimmay n cal went dt nape to go to lou melnatis for some cookie dessert thing..then we came bk to lisle, stopped at my house then went to mcdonalds. the homeless lady that we see everywhere was sitting outside at one of the tables. patty saw her shaving her head..and like just cutting it really deep with the razor..i felt so bad. but then my sister told me nicole lenke gave her money and she didnt even say thank you or anything. everyone says like that she has a mental problem or something..idk..we were just like watching her cause she was just like yelling really loud..at no one..it was kinda scary..i felt bad but then she was smoking..so if you have money to smoke cigarettes then...yeah. but then we saw colleen and kelsey and they were just pulling around the parking lot watching her too so it was kinda funny. then we left and went to get this one sign in someones yard that maggz had to have. it said 'IM GORGEOUS INSIDE' because i guess the house was for sale or something. so she took that and then we decided to use the sticks from the sign as marshmallow sticks so we went to callis and had a bonfire with ourselves and jumped on her tramp and talked. twas very fun i must say except we were getting eaten alive. we were just talking about guys n stuff...somehow we got on the subject of kimms and how shell get the guy to notice her and stuff but then she never makes that second move onto something more..and i was thinking..thats exactly how i am...i hate being the one to make the first move with most things..i dont really like planning things and i dont like calling ppl...but i guess if theres a guy and hes the same way as me..nothing will ever happen..so me and kim said we gotta tough it up and just go for it...ehh..maybe lol. homecoming weekend is gonna be the shittt.were already planning it all out now, can you say losers? so thursdays my birfday so were partying it up!!! then friday no school and the homecoming football game..&& partying!!! then saturdays homecoming!!! && partying!!!!1 then sunday..after party...&& more partying!!1 then monday no school..so parrrty! hahah what can i say? we aint got as much bounce as california but we do like to party alllll the time..hehe =)im pretty siked for this school year idk why..i like seeing everyone all the time && stuff. and i cannot wait til basketball season OMFG. its gonna be insane..just like last year playin with all the old sophies!! god i loved it. we were so fucking good and will be this year too! varsity hoesss && were gettin fleeces that me and kels designed ohh boy lol my schedules kinda hard this year so im gonna try and stay focused and actually do my homework n stuff..well see how long that lasts lol leaving for vegas on wednesday til sunday..kinda sucks cause its the last week of summer but its fucking vegas and tobey keith concert so its all good. && for school shopping for clothes my mom usually takes us all at the same time but this year were goin separately..THANK GOD...so mi and my mommy are gonna go to fox valley while ash's workin and get major discounts at abercrombieeee wooooo hooooo alright full house is callin my name again..im pathetic but whatcha gon do? XOOX

*10th grade - As I sat there in English class, I stared at the girl next to me. She was my so called "best friend". I stared at her long, silky hair, and wished she was MINE. But she didn't think of me like that, and I knew it. After class, she walked up to me and asked me for the notes she had missed the day before and I handed them to her. She said "thanks" and gave me a kiss on the cheek. I wanted to tell her, I WANT her to know that I don't want to be just friends, I love her but I'm just too shy, and I don't know why.

*11th grade - The phone rang. On the other end, it was her. She was in tears, mumbling on and on about how her love had broke her heart. She asked me to come over because she didn't want to be ALONE, so I did. As I sat next to her on the sofa, I stared at her soft eyes, wishing she was MINE. After 1 hour, two Drew Barrymore movies, and three bags of chips, she decided to go to sleep. She looked at me, said "thanks" and gave me a kiss on the cheek. I want to tell her, I WANT her to know that I don't want to be just friends, I love her but I'm just too shy, and I don't know why.

*Senior year - The day before prom she walked to my locker. "My date is sick" she said; "he's not going to go." I didn't have a date, and in 7th grade, we made a promise that if neither of us had dates, we would go together just as "best friends". So we DID. Prom night, after EVERYTHING was over, I was standing at her front door step! I stared at her as she smiled at me and stared at me with her crystal eyes. I want her to be mine, but she doesn't think of me like that, and I KNOW it. Then she said "I had the best time, thanks!" and gave me a kiss on the cheek. I want to tell her, I WANT her to know that I don't want to be just friends, I love her but I'm just too shy, and I don't know why.

*Graduation Day - A day passed, then a week, then a month. Before I could blink, it was graduation day. I watched as her perfect body floated like an angel up on stage to get her diploma. I wanted her to be MINE, but she didn't think of me like that, and I knew it. Before everyone went home, she came to me in her smock and hat, and cried as I hugged her. Then she lifted her head from my shoulder and said, "you're my best friend, thanks" and gave me a kiss on the cheek. I want to tell her, I WANT her to know that I don't want to be just friends, I love her but I'm just too shy, and I don't know why.

*A Few Years Later - Now I SIT in the pews of the church. That girl is getting married now. I watched her say "I do" and drive off to her new life, married TO another man. I wanted her to be MINE, but she didn`t see me like that, and I knew it. But before she drove away, she came to me and said "You came!". She said "thanks" and kissed me on the cheek. I want to tell her, I WANT her to know that I don't want to be just friends, I love her but I'm just too shy, and I don't know why.

*Funeral - YEARS passed, I looked down at the coffin of a girl who used to be my "best friend". At the service, they read a diary entry she had WROTE in her high school years. This is what it read: I stare at him wishing he was MINE, but he doesn't think of me like that, and I know it. I want to tell him, I want him to KNOW that I don't want to be just friends, I LOVE him but I'm just too shy, and I don't know why. I wished he would tell me he LOVED me! I wish I did too... I thought to MYSELF, and I cried. <33
